<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="163" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1414,1991]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1414,1439]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Metope elongate, with distinct median and sublateral carinae joined in one point on its upper margin (
<bibRefCitation box="[158,468,1450,1475]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" refId="ref5415" refString="Doering, K. C. (1938) A contribution to the taxonomy of the subfamily Issinae in America north of Mexico (Fulgoridae, Homoptera). Part 2. The University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 25 (20), 447 - 575." type="journal article">Doering 1938, Pl. 52: 8, 10</bibRefCitation>
). Coryphe elongate, with distinct median carina running from its anterior margin to its middle; anterior margin acutely angulately convex (
<bibRefCitation box="[752,1065,1486,1511]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" refId="ref5415" refString="Doering, K. C. (1938) A contribution to the taxonomy of the subfamily Issinae in America north of Mexico (Fulgoridae, Homoptera). Part 2. The University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 25 (20), 447 - 575." type="journal article">Doering 1938, Pl. 51: 2, 5</bibRefCitation>
). Second and third segments of rostrum are almost equal in length; third segment narrowing apically (
<figureCitation box="[960,1046,1522,1547]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–18" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1811,1834]" captionTargetBox="[598,999,917,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[588,1011,914,1800]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17–18. Thioniina, rostrum in lateral view. 17—Cheiloceps musca Uhler; 18—Fowlerium naso (Fowler)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1290896/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Fore wings elongate, surpassing abdomen, with narrow hypocostal plate. Forewing vein sequence: R 2, furcating near to basal cell; M 2, furcating before wing middle; CuΑ 1. Clavus long, open—Pcu+Α1 runs into apex of clavus. Pcu fusing Α1 after middle of clavus. Hind wings 3-lobed, with deep cubital and anal clefts and without coupling lobe on its anterior margin. CuΑ2 and CuP not fused apically, but connected by several transverse veins (
<figureCitation box="[1030,1163,1669,1694]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–13" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1555,1578]" captionTargetBox="[487,1103,495,1517]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[464,1123,477,1534]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–13. Fowlerium spp., hind wing. 12—F. naso (Fowler); 13—F. productum (Van Duzee)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1290892/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Figs 12, 13</figureCitation>
). Pcu and Α1.1 not fused medially, free. Hindwing sequence: R 2 r-m 1 M 1 m-cua 1 CuΑ 2 cua-cup 2-5 CuP 1 cup-pcu 1 Pcu 3 pcu-a1 1 Α1 2 Α2 2–4. Hind tibia with 2 lateral spines. First metatarsomere with a whole row of spines arranged in arc. Ventral aedeagal hooks slightly furcating subapically (
<bibRefCitation box="[675,1009,1785,1810]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" refId="ref5415" refString="Doering, K. C. (1938) A contribution to the taxonomy of the subfamily Issinae in America north of Mexico (Fulgoridae, Homoptera). Part 2. The University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 25 (20), 447 - 575." type="journal article">Doering, 1938, Pl. 55: 1, 7, 8</bibRefCitation>
). Ovipositor with rounded gonoplacs. Hind margin of VII sternum with large semicircular process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="163" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1414,1991]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1857,1882]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Etymology.</emphasis>
Genus named in honor of famous British entomologist William Weeks Fowler (
<date box="[1243,1372,1858,1882]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" value="1849" valueMax="1923">1849–1923</date>
) who describing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1905" box="[274,421,1893,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Thionia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="naso">
<emphasis box="[274,421,1893,1918]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Thionia naso</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had doubts on its generic position already (
<bibRefCitation box="[910,1115,1893,1918]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" refId="ref5620" refString="Fowler, W. W. (1905) Family Issidae. Order Rhynchota. Suborder Hemiptera-Homoptera. Insecta (Continued). Biologia Centrali-Americana; contributions to the knowledge of the fauna and flora of Mexico and Central America, 1, 113 - 129." type="journal article">Fowler 1905: 125</bibRefCitation>
). Neuter in gender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1414,1991]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,359,1929,1954]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Composition.</emphasis>
In addition to type species 
<taxonomicName authority="Van Duzee, 1908" authorityName="Van Duzee" authorityYear="1908" box="[670,1067,1929,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Thionia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="producta">
<emphasis box="[670,865,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Thionia producta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[873,1067,1930,1954]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" refId="ref6870" refString="Van Duzee, E. P. (1908) Studies in North American Fulgoridae. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 1907, 467 - 498." type="proceedings paper">Van Duzee, 1908</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Doering, 1941" authorityName="Doering" authorityYear="1941" box="[1123,1383,1929,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Thionia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acuta">
<emphasis box="[1123,1213,1931,1954]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">T. acuta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1220,1383,1929,1954]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" refId="ref5463" refString="Doering, K. C. (1941) A contribution to the taxonomy of the subfamily Issinae in America north of Mexico (Fulgoridae, Homoptera). Part 4. The University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 27 (10), 185 - 233." type="journal article">Doering, 1941</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also belong to this genus.
</paragraph>
